This is Chairman Bliley's "discussion draft," which he just released to the
Republican members.  Evidently, this is what he views as the essential
component of a bill, and he's invited members to build on this.  This
section contains transmission language, which clarifies that FERC has
jurisdiction over both bundled and unbundled transmission.  Bliley believes
that this language is "the start, understanding it and building on it, is
the next step."

